# GOV.UK Prototype Kit Cursor Rules

## General Principles
- You are an expert in GDS (Government Digital Service) design standards and the GOV.UK Prototype Kit.
- Prioritize accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA) in all generated code.
- Use the GOV.UK Design System components and patterns.

## HTML & Nunjucks (.html)
<!-- - Use Nunjucks templates (`.html` files) instead of raw HTML when possible.-->
- Always extend `layouts/new-nav.html.html` (this project's base layout).
<!-- - Use macros for components (e.g., `govukInput`, `govukButton`). -->
- Do not create custom CSS for elements covered by the GOV.UK frontend library.

## Styling & Components
- Use `govuk-frontend` classes.
- Use `govuk-!-margin-*` and `govuk-!-padding-*` helper classes for spacing, not custom CSS.
- Ensure all forms use proper error handling and input validation styling.

## Content
- Use simple, direct language (Plain English).
- Do not use exclamation marks.
- Follow GOV.UK tone of voice.

## Code Structure
- Follow the structure of the `app` folder.
- Keep `routes.js` clean; create new route files for specific user journeys if necessary.
